review: Ive been using Insta for about 5-6 years now and it has been pretty decent since I first started up my art account(s). I made a bunch of friends within the art community and what not, which I why I liked this app quite a bit. However, recently, Ive kinda grown a disliking towards IG- I have noticed that there are tons of updates, it seems like once or twice a week I check and IG needs and update, which annoys me because these updates don’t change a thing about the app (and when it does, it just moves on or two features around). And, on the topic of updates, the one with the notes feature didn’t add the feature to my main account and put it on an account I barely even use instead- I sent in two complaints/reports about this almost a month or two ago and nothing has come out of it. (Also, I from what I am hearing, the notes feature is gone so I guess this is no longer a major issue?) And this is not the first time Ive had an issue like this. There have been multiple updates before in the past year or two where the new features only go to the account I don’t really use, which annoys me because I have sent in reports about it before yet I still have the same problem. Also, recently there have been quite a few bugs/lags with the app, which is becoming more frequent- I guess sum it up, this app needs some serious fixing- It was just fine (for me anyways) before the past update or two, but now its just crappy-

Though Instagram is one of the simplest social media platforms you could have the support is complete trash. I spent the last two weeks trying to recover my account that was registered as compromised for unfollowing people. A little back story I have had this account for over 7+ years and I hadn’t really done much with it and in a failed effort to make the account more recent I encountered several inappropriate post of nudity and etc. I spent many many many hours reporting post that were inappropriate for the app that is 13+  and I decided to clean out the people I was following bc I was sick of the disturbing things I seen on there. I found that my account followed 100’s of people I didn’t know and of course I change my password frequently to keep from scam so I knew that wasn’t the problem. While unfollowing said accounts and many others I got a page saying. “Account compromised.” That I some how purchased followers against the guidelines I was sitting at a total of like 100 followers or so, plus the whole idea of buying followers is lost on me. I have spent two weeks trying to get this resolved. Instagram has little to no support with simple Q & A forms for assistance that just DO NOT WORK! It has become completely ridiculous and I’m not the only person I know who has had this issue. Regardless. The app has gone down hill and hopefully will get it’s crap together in the near future.
title: Newest owners of the application have messed it up!

review: I absolutely love instagram. I love scrolling through feed and stories a lot. But, anymore, when I do that there’s so many graphic posts that made its way into my feed somehow. It’s disgusting. It’s thinks from completely naked women (or women in only fishnets) trying to sell themselves all the way to the most recent post, a guy shooting another guy with a rifle in the head (with NO graphic post warning). I understand that instagram doesn’t have a lot of control of what people post when they do, but I’ve reported more posts like these than I can count in the last few months with absolutely no response from instagram. I’m extremely disappointed. I don’t need to see posts like this and neither do 13 year olds who use this app. Most of the time, it’s meme/funny pages that are associated with these posts, but it’s not actually them because they’re tagged in it somehow so I can see it. So no matter how many pages I block, another one will pop up just because I want to see quotes! I can’t go through 5 posts on my page without seeing these things. Instagram, PLEASE take this feature away. PLEASE save everyone from seeing these awful posts. At the least, PLEASE give me a response to my reports. I know for a fact other people are reporting them, and I want to know that at least 1 of the 150 posts I’ve reported so far has been taken down. MAKE INSTAGRAM KID FRIENDLY AGAIN!! At least to where I don’t lose my appetite.
title: Reporting posts

review: Look, I get it. You want me to engage with your app for longer durations and with greater frequency. If you can get me to do that your ads are worth more. Makes sense. So you inundate me with ML suggested posts and high view count reels. I click on some of them, i even share them, but I hate them. I come to interact with your platform because I want to connect to friends and creators, makers, engineers and artists that I admire. I come to it to feel community or be inspired, but more and more recently i just keep getting pummeled with pimple popping or sexually suggestive tattoo videos or “dermatologist reactions“ and i get drawn in and i get distracted from why I’m really there. I know this is exactly what you intend. You do this because its easy. Just let the models push content that drives interaction instead of stuff the users are seeking out (following) on their own. You really should be ashamed of yourselves. You have something really great and you just keep poisoning it because the only accountability that matters is revenue. It’s shareholder value. It’s the thing that gets you incremental gains in your performance reviews. You train us to want more; you feed on our loneliness, our want to be connected. You wound us for pennies. We just keep coming back but it doesn’t change how bad it makes us feel. I pity you.
title: No more Suggested posts/reels please

review:
So many stupid, unhelpful updates lately. We all know Instagram has been trying to become more like Tiktok, and I hate its overemphasis on reels now. It used to just be a platform of photo-sharing, and this is what made users like it and is what we want. But my explore page is just always filled with reels, and whenever I click on a (often new) user’s profile it automatically goes straight to just showing reels. It doesn’t reflect their profile, I want to see ALL their posts—the regular, curated profile with all their photos and content. If I wanted to see reels I could click the Reels button myself. It’s just a constance annoyance—clicking a user, seeing weird feel thumbnails, being confused, then realizing and having to click to the first tab.

Moreover, it’s the constant promotions and advertising that Instagram has begun been throwing in your face, all so they can be more profitable. As I’m scrolling on my feed after a while ALL I see just become suggested post after suggested post. If I wanted to “explore” other posts I’d go to the Explore tab, Instagram. I’m on MY feed to see friends and users that I follow. Why do you continually interrupt this with your constant suggestions (which I know are promotions accounts can pay for and earn them more money)?

Like everyone has been saying, we just the old Instagram back. Please.
title: disappointing updates
